net.enilink.komma.em.internal

Class CachedEntity

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.enilink.komma.em.internal.CachedEntity

  • public class CachedEntity
extends Object
    A wrapper for caching a specific RDF resource (entity) with its properties in different contexts (named graphs or models).

    • Method Detail

      • put

        public Object put(Object context,
                  Object property,
                  Object value)
        Associates the specified value with the specified property for an entity in this cache. If the entity previously contained a mapping for this context, the old value is replaced by the specified value.
        Parameters:
        context - context to the entity to be accessed.
        property - property with which the specified value is to be associated.
        value - value to be associated with the specified property.
        Returns:
        previous value associated with specified property, or null if there was no mapping for property.

      • remove

        public Object remove(Object context,
                     Object property)
        Removes the mapping for this context from a entity. Returns the value to which the entity previously associated the property, or null if the entity contained no mapping for this property.
        Parameters:
        context - context to the entity to be accessed.
        property - property whose mapping is to be removed from the entity
        Returns:
        previous value associated with specified entity's property

      • clearProperties

        Removes all data of the entity for the given context.
        Parameters:
        context - context for the entity to remove
        Returns:
        true if the data was removed, false if the data was not found
